erned about the prolonged recession, it probably does not seriously impact on the living of individuals. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Table 5. Q: If general elections are held today, which party would you vote | |for? (%) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Party |Feb 94 |Feb 93 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |LDP |22.6 |37.7 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |JNP |11.5 |N/A | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |SDPJ |8.2 |N/A | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Shinseito |5.6 |---- (Shinseito was foun-| | | |ded in June 93) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Komeito |3.6 |N/A | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |JCP |2.8 |N/A | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Sakigake |1.8 |---- (Sakigake was found-| | | |ed in June 93) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |DSP |1.2 |N/A | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Others |2.4 |N/A | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Any oPposition |N/A |29.2 (except 2 new parti-| | | |es) | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Will Abstain |4.4 |5.3 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Undecided |35.9 |27.8 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Table 6. Q: To what degree are you satisfied with the current political situation? (%) Date Very Generally Don't Somewhat Very Satisfied Satisfied Care/Don't Dissatisfied Dissatisfied Know Mar 0.3 11.9 8.8 39.6 39.4 93 Apr 0.3 13.8 8.6 46.1 31.2 May 0.3 14.4 12.6 42.5 30.2 Jun 0.5 15.1 12.8 44.9 26.6 Jul 0.3 14.3 9.8 44.5 31.0 Aug 0.5 20.9 17.7 42.1 18.9 Sep 0.6 28.4 20.3 40.1 10.5 Oct 0.5 26.0 12.9 46.7 13.9 Nov 0.6 26.3 17.0 43.6 12.5 Dec N/A N/A N/A N/A N/A Jan 0.4 22.7 14.3 47.2 15.5 94 Feb 0.6 22.5 13.1 47.9 15.9 Pollees' Voting Intentions The top three popular parties were the LDP, the JNP, and the SDPJ. Compared with the January survey, support for Shinseito dropped by 2 percent. NOTE: The survey, conducted by Chuo Research Inc. on 10-13 February, was carried on as individual interviews of 2,000 eligible voters picked at random. Responses were obtained from 68.1 percent of, or 1,361, pollees. Data belong to the Multipurpose Statistic Databank of Tsukuba University.
